The paper discusses the emergence of computational intelligence in an acellular organism, specifically the slime mould Physarum polycephalum. The paper uses laboratory experiments and computer modelling techniques to investigate the role of the plasmodial cytoskeleton in facilitating intelligent behaviour. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.BI (Bioinformatics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.RO (Robotics).
